{'id': 'cb0c9c98-4eb3-3ed7-ac05-8643e3926ed0', 'contentType': 'STORY', 'title': "India's TCS jumps 6% as CEO signals potential demand revival", 'description': '', 'summary': "(Reuters) -Shares of India's Tata Consultancy Services rose 6% on Friday, set for the best day since July, as investors overlooked the company's tepid performance in North America and focused on the CEO's remarks signalling a potential revival in demand.
